description._content: Description: The main stores at M.-i-S. to which supplies of all kinds are brought by rail from D.-i-K. on the Karun River. The crane is unloading a motor chassis. Description: Drilling Stores at M.-i-S. Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
